.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Timestamp \- NIP\-03 OpenTimestamps attestations for events
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Timestamp;
\&
\&    # Create a timestamp attestation
\&    my $ts = Net::Nostr::Timestamp\->new(
\&        pubkey    => $my_pubkey,
\&        event_id  => $target_event_id,
\&        kind      => 1,
\&        ots_data  => $ots_base64,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,    # optional
\&    );
\&    my $event = $ts\->to_event;
\&    $key\->sign_event($event);
\&    $client\->publish($event);
\&
\&    # Parse a received timestamp attestation
\&    my $ts2 = Net::Nostr::Timestamp\->from_event($event);
\&    say $ts2\->event_id;   # target event ID
\&    say $ts2\->kind;        # target event kind
\&    say $ts2\->ots_data;    # base64\-encoded OTS proof
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-03 OpenTimestamps attestations. A timestamp attestation is a
kind 1040 event containing an OpenTimestamps <https://opentimestamps.org/>
proof for another event.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR field contains the full base64\-encoded \f(CW\*(C`.ots\*(C'\fR file data. The
proof MUST prove the referenced event ID as its digest. The \f(CW\*(C`.ots\*(C'\fR file
SHOULD contain a single Bitcoin attestation and no pending attestations.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 7
\&    my $ts = Net::Nostr::Timestamp\->new(
\&        pubkey    => $pubkey_hex,
\&        event_id  => $target_event_id,
\&        kind      => 1,
\&        ots_data  => $ots_base64,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,  # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new timestamp attestation. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`event_id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`kind\*(C'\fR, and
\&\f(CW\*(C`ots_data\*(C'\fR are required. \f(CW\*(C`relay_url\*(C'\fR is optional and will be included in
the \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag if provided. Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $ts = Net::Nostr::Timestamp\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 1040 event into a Timestamp object. Croaks if the event is
not kind 1040.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    my $ts = Net::Nostr::Timestamp\->from_event($event);
\&    say $ts\->event_id;
\&    say $ts\->ots_data;
.Ve
.SH METHODS
.IX Header "METHODS"
.SS to_event
.IX Subsection "to_event"
.Vb 2
\&    my $event = $ts\->to_event;
\&    my $event = $ts\->to_event(created_at => time());
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1040 Net::Nostr::Event from the timestamp attestation.
Extra arguments are passed through to the Event constructor.
.SS event_id
.IX Subsection "event_id"
.Vb 1
\&    my $id = $ts\->event_id;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the target event ID referenced by the \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag.
.SS kind
.IX Subsection "kind"
.Vb 1
\&    my $kind = $ts\->kind;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the target event kind from the \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag.
.SS ots_data
.IX Subsection "ots_data"
.Vb 1
\&    my $data = $ts\->ots_data;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the base64\-encoded OpenTimestamps proof data.
.SS pubkey
.IX Subsection "pubkey"
.Vb 1
\&    my $pk = $ts\->pubkey;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the pubkey of the attestation author.
.SS relay_url
.IX Subsection "relay_url"
.Vb 1
\&    my $url = $ts\->relay_url;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the relay URL from the \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if none was provided.
